            "heading": "Saree Style Spotlight: 'Aap Jaisa Koi' on Netflix",
            "text": "<p>Netflix's <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aap_Jaisa_Koi_(film)\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><em>Aap Jaisa Koi</em></span><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"> (2025)</span></a> offers a refreshing take on middle-aged romance, with R. Madhavan and Fatima Sana Shaikh delivering compelling performances. Beyond the narrative, the film's sartorial choices, particularly Fatima's saree ensembles, stand out as a testament to Bengali elegance and contemporary flair.</p><h2>Fatima Sana Shaikh's Saree Aesthetics</h2><p>Fatima's portrayal of Madhu Bose, a French instructor from Kolkata, is accentuated by her impeccable saree choices. Each drape not only complements her character's persona but also pays homage to traditional Bengali attire.</p>",
